  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 800 mg
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel, halve, and thinly slice @red onion{1%unit}. Mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP minced onion. Core, seed, and thinly slice @yellow bell peppers{1%unit} and @green bell pepper{1%unit}. Core, then finely chop @roma tomatoes{2%unit}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Cut @lime{1%unit} in half; cut one half into wedges.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and bell peppers. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing occasionally, until softened and charred in spots, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Combine tomatoes, half the cilantro, minced onion, juice from lime half, and a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Pat @beef stir-fry{20%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add beef and season with @fajita spice blend{2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{12%unit} in a damp paper towel and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven for 5 minutes at 400 degrees.

Divide @cheddar cheese{1%cup} between tortillas, then top each with the beef, veggies, and salsa. Dollop with @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over.